 Evaluate $f(-2)$.
\begin{aligned}
f(-2) &= \frac{3(-2)-2}{-2-2} \\
&= \frac{-6-2}{-4} \\
&= \frac{-8}{-4} \\
&= 2
\end{aligned}

## Step 2: Evaluate $f(-1)$.
\begin{aligned}
f(-1) &= \frac{3(-1)-2}{-1-2} \\
&= \frac{-3-2}{-3} \\
&= \frac{-5}{-3} \\
&= \frac{5}{3}
\end{aligned}

## Step 3: Evaluate $f(0)$.
\begin{aligned}
f(0) &= \frac{3(0)-2}{0-2} \\
&= \frac{0-2}{-2} \\
&= \frac{-2}{-2} \\
&= 1
\end{aligned}

## Step 4: Sum $f(-2)$, $f(-1)$, and $f(0)$.
\begin{aligned}
f(-2) + f(-1) + f(0) &= 2 + \frac{5}{3} + 1 \\
&= 2 + \frac{5}{3} + \frac{3}{3} \\
&= 2 + \frac{5}{3} + \frac{3}{3} \\
&= \frac{6}{3} + \frac{5}{3} + \frac{3}{3} \\
&= \frac{6+5+3}{3} \\
&= \frac{14}{3}
\end{aligned}

Therefore, the final answer is: $\boxed{\frac{14}{3}}$.

